    "comment": "Rationale: - K+-channel tetramerization domain-containing proteins (KCTDs) are auxiliary GABAB receptor (GBR) subunits.\n- Experiments were performed at the synaptic connection from medial habenula (MHb) to interpeduncular nucleus (IPN).\n- pre-embedding immunogold labeling, imaged with TEM. \"In MHb terminals in the rostral IPN, Cav2.3 and KCTD12b showed similar localization patterns, with peak particle densities in the active zone and a gradual decrease in density with increased distance from the active zone (Figure 3A,E).\"\n\n- Figure 2C: immunolabeling of WT and KCTD12b KO mice shows antibody specificity. Experimental description: Wild-type C57BL/6J mice(Jax, Bar Harbor, ME; #000664) purchased from Jackson Laboratory.\nPotassium channel tetramerisation domain-containing 12b\nAntibody: anti-KCTD12b (polyclonal, raised against a synthetic peptide comprised of the N-terminal amino acids 1-16 of KCTD12b) (1 ug/ul, 1 O/N, Bettler lab, Univ. Basel)",
